        <updateDate>2009-04-03T20:35:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Healthcare Enhancement for Local Public Servants Act of 2009<tt> - </tt>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) extend eligibility for tax-free distributions from governmental employee benefit plans for health and long-term care insurance to any retired state or local public employee (currently, limited to retired public safety officers); (2) provide for a tax deduction of such distributions rather than an exclusion from gross income; (3) allow nonitemizing taxpayers to claim such tax deduction; and (4) allow an annual inflation adjustment to the $3,000 distribution limit beginning after 2009. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
